cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.CR 

The paper deals with computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques to improve the performance of driver drowsiness detection systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for data augmentation, which falls under the category of ML, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of population bias visualisation strategy, which is related to fairness and ethics in AI, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also deals with human-computer interaction (HCI) as it aims to improve the performance of driver drowsiness detection systems, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another possible category. Finally, the paper also discusses the potential biases in the datasets used for training the models, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
